<h3><a href="/news/2010/10/01/ab-12-gives-foster-kids-hope/" class="news-link">Governor signs bill extending age for foster care youth</a></h3>

<p>
    <a href="/news/2010/10/01/ab-12-gives-foster-kids-hope/">
        <img src="http://media.scpr.org/images/2010/09/24/fostercare_th.jpg" class="offlede-thumb" />
    </a>    
    AB12, the California Fostering Connections to Success Act, will allow foster youth to receive benefits for three additional years to age 21. The measure aims to protect youth from many harsh realities they faced on their own after "aging-out" of the system at 18.
