        <h3><a href="/programs/patt-morrison/2010/10/01/ab12-signed/" class="news-link">The power of 3 extra years: AB12 to the rescue of California’s foster youth</a></h3>
        <p>
            <a href="/programs/patt-morrison/2010/10/01/ab12-signed/">
                <img src="http://media.scpr.org/images/2010/09/23/foster_care_group_th.png" class="offlede-thumb" />
            </a>
      Foster kids at 18 are more likely to be homelessness, incarcerated, or addicted to drugs than the average teen. Yesterday Gov. Schwarzenegger signed AB12 which allows foster youth to stay in the system until they are 21. Can three extra years help the thousands of foster kids manage the difficult transition into independent adulthood?
